                     Radiosonde Replacement System Info

CAVEAT:  The following software has successfully been compiled and 
executed in an IBM RISC/6000 UNIX environment.  There are no guarantees
that it can be compile and/or executed in any environment.  

This software is in the public domain, furnished "as is", without 
technical support, and with no warranty, expressed or implied, as
to its usefulness for any purpose.


Software.

   BUFR Decoder Program:   bufr_1_05.f

      Create Object File:  xlf -c bufr_1_05.f

      This software is vital for operational software to perform the
      decoding of BUFR coded message files.  This software is a library
      of subroutines.


-----------------------------------------------
   BUFR fix program for UNIX:  grabbufr.f

      Compilation:  xlf -o grabbufr.exe bufr_1_05.o grabbufr.f

      In order to read a BUFR data file in a UNIX environment, this 
      software must be run to copy an original BUFR file provided by
      the NWS to another BUFR type file.

      The function of the program is to reformat the binary green words 
      at the beginning and ending of each record.

      Usage:  [path]grabbufr.exe  <InputBUFRfile>  <OutputBUFRfile>


-----------------------------------------------
   BUFR verbose dump program:  DumpData.f

      Compilation:  xlf -o DumpData.exe bufr_1_05.o DumpData.f

      This program reads a BUFR data file and generates a dump file of
      each data value, one value per line.  All seven data messages 
      are written to one file.  

      NOTE:  An output file can easily reach 100 to 200 MB.

      This program expects the input file to be called "rrs.bfr" 
      and the output to be called "rrs.out".  In UNIX the following
      command can be used to create soft links to data filenames.

      ln -s <input_BUFR_file> rrs.bfr 
      ln -s <output_text_file> rrs.out

      Usage:  [path]DumpData.exe


-----------------------------------------------
   Split dump file program:  split_dump.f 

      Compilation:  xlf -o split_dump.exe split_dump.f

      This program divides the output from DumpData into seven data
      message files:  
      NC002019.DMP - Metadata,
      NC002020.DMP - RRS raw PTU,
      NC002021.DMP - RRS raw GPS unsmoothed,
      NC002022.DMP - RRS raw GPS smoothed,
      NC002023.DMP - RRS processed PTU,
      NC002024.DMP - RRS processed GPS,
      NC002025.DMP - RRS standard & significant levels.


----------------------------------------------
   RRS decode BUFR to Formatted Text Records:  rrs_decoder.f

      Compilation:  xlf -o rrs_decoder.exe bufr_1_05.o rrs_decoder.f
       
      This program reads a BUFR data file and writes decoded data
      to seven files.  It is intended as a tool for someone wishing
      to decode one or more message types into fixed record formats.

      The seven output message type files are:
      NC002019.DAT - Metadata,
      NC002020.DAT - RRS raw PTU,
      NC002021.DAT - RRS raw GPS unsmoothed,
      NC002022.DAT - RRS raw GPS smoothed,
      NC002023.DAT - RRS processed PTU,
      NC002024.DAT - RRS processed GPS,
      NC002025.DAT - RRS standard & significant levels.

    
---------------------------------------------
   Heading descriptions for rrs_decoder:  rrs_decoder.hdg

 
